<title>USA: Ford Motor to issue $500 mln in 100-yr bonds.</title>
<headline>Ford Motor to issue $500 mln in 100-yr bonds.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ford Motor Co is expected to issue a $500 million 100-year bond offering said Bear Stearns &amp; Co Inc, the lead underwriter for the deal.</p>
<p>The A1/A-plus rated century offering, which is expected to price on Thursday, is noncallable for life, they said.</p>
<p>Unofficial price talk on the issue is seen at 85 basis points over Treasuries, dealers said.</p>
<p>Ford Motor Co, based in Dearborn, Michigan, is the world's second largest automobile manufacturer.</p>
<p>(( -- Nancy Leinfuss, 212-859-1675 ))</p>
